    b"   {{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Choose memory search hints for the selected"
    b" task and current request.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before "
    b"the selected task runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once the hints look good enough for the "
    b"request without thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a       "
    b" - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings."
    b"contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a"
    b" substring against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact t"
    b"ext values. Each value is checked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchab"
    b"le memory content.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        "
    b"- candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a    "
    b"      preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and option"
    b"al candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; "
    b"a memory can be useful\x0d\x0a          when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0d"
    b"\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_"
    b"of empty unless compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags."
    b"none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable w"
    b"ords or phrases that should appear\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0d\x0a       "
    b" - Use strings.equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0d\x0a        "
    b"  memory value as a whole.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints ov"
    b"er broad keyword stuffing.\x0d\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful search "
    b"hint is available.\x0d\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0d\x0a\x0d"
